ustrations, Pat Shipman's To the Heart of the Nile is an extraordinary achievement -- an unforgettable portrait of an unforgettable woman; a story of discovery, bravery, determination, and love, meticulously reconstructed through journals, documents, and private papers, and told in the inimitable narrative style that has already won this author resounding international acclaim.", 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/55/54/9780060505554.jpg', 'title_long': 'To the Heart of the Nile: Lady Florence Baker and the Exploration of Central Africa', 'edition': '1', 'dimensions': 'Height: 9.5 Inches, Length: 6.5 Inches, Weight: 0.73 Pounds, Width: 1.5 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 6.5}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 1.5}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 0.73}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 9.5}}, 'pages': 448, 'date_published': '2004-02-03', 'subjects': ['Biographies & Memoirs', 'Historical', 'United States', 'Africa', 'Travelers & Explorers', 'History', 'Americas'], 'authors': ['Pat Shipman'], 'title': 'To the Heart of the Nile: Lady Florence Baker and the Exploration of Central Africa', 'isbn13': '9780060505554', 'msrp': 25.95, 'binding': 'Hardcover', 'isbn': '0060505559', 'isbn10': '0060505559'}}